## Creating virtual environment

```shell
# System global (if not installed)
pip install setuptools virtualenv virtualenvwrapper-win

# Project local:
python -m virtualenv -p C:\Python27\python.exe .venv
call .venv/Scripts/activate
virtualenv .venv
.venv/bin/activate

# Install all requirements:
pip install -r requirements-dev.txt
pip install -r requirements.txt
# More pip examples:
pip install Flask==1.0.2
pip freeze Flask
pip freeze > requirements.txt
```

## Demo flask server

- Set flask env: `set FLASK_APP=server/server.py:app` (or add into `.flaskenv`)
- Run in console: `flask run`
- Open `http://127.0.0.1:5000/`

